{#- ═══ CALC ISLAND — the .calc widget markup is preserved VERBATIM (tb-formula.js
    binds to data-calc / data-formula / data-calc-num / data-out — class restyle of
    the result CTA is behavior-safe). id="calc" kept so the hero anchor lands. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="calc">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The worksheet</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Work out your monthly budget.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:66ch;">Enter your figures; the result updates as you type. Everything stays in your browser &mdash; nothing is sent until <em>you</em> decide to book a call.</p>

    <div class="calc" data-calc data-formula="budget">
      <form class="calc__form" aria-describedby="calc-disclaimer-top">
        <p class="calc__formnote" id="calc-disclaimer-top">Plain math on your own numbers &mdash; not advice.</p>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="f-income">Monthly revenue <span class="intake-field__optional">$</span></label>
          <input type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="any" id="f-income" data-calc-num="income" placeholder="e.g. 40000">
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="f-cogs">Cost of goods / services <span class="intake-field__optional">direct costs &mdash; $</span></label>
          <input type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="any" id="f-cogs" data-calc-num="cogs" placeholder="e.g. 14000">
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="f-fixed">Fixed operating costs <span class="intake-field__optional">rent, salaries, software &mdash; $</span></label>
          <input type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="any" id="f-fixed" data-calc-num="fixed" placeholder="e.g. 18000">
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="f-other">Other / variable costs <span class="intake-field__optional">marketing, travel, misc &mdash; $</span></label>
          <input type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="any" id="f-other" data-calc-num="other" placeholder="e.g. 3000">
        </div>
      </form>

      <div class="calc__result" id="calc-result" role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <p class="calc__result-label">Monthly surplus / deficit</p>
        <p class="calc__result-range"><span data-out="primary">&mdash;</span></p>
        <ul class="calc__metrics">
          <li class="calc__metric"><span class="calc__metric-label">Total monthly expenses</span><span class="calc__metric-value" data-out="m1">&mdash;</span></li>
          <li class="calc__metric"><span class="calc__metric-label">Net margin</span><span class="calc__metric-value" data-out="m2">&mdash;</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="calc__result-why" data-out="text">Enter your monthly revenue and the three expense lines above.</p>
        <p class="calc__result-disclaimer">This is <strong>a model of your own inputs</strong>, not financial advice. A real budget tracks against actuals each month and forecasts forward &mdash; a Certified ProAdvisor can build that on your books.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-cta calc__result-cta" href="/contact/?intent=accounting" data-ga="cta_click" data-tb-event="calc_to_quote" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;height:50px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:12px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Book the discovery call</a>
      </div>

      <noscript>
        <div class="calc__noscript">
          <p>The live worksheet needs JavaScript. The math is simple: <strong>surplus = revenue − (cost of goods + fixed costs + other costs)</strong>, and net margin = surplus ÷ revenue. Or <a href="/contact/?intent=accounting">book a free discovery call</a> and a ProAdvisor will build a budget with you.</p>
        </div>
      </noscript>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ═══ HOW IT WORKS — no-black-box prose + the flow diagram (preserved verbatim).
    sand alt band. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="budget-calc-how" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">No black box</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2">How the worksheet works.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The arithmetic is deliberately simple so you can trust it. <strong>Total expenses = cost of goods + fixed operating costs + other/variable costs.</strong> <strong>Surplus or deficit = revenue − total expenses.</strong> <strong>Net margin = surplus ÷ revenue</strong>, shown as a percentage. Splitting costs into those three buckets is enough to see whether the month works and where the weight sits.</p>
      <p>Cost of goods (or cost of services) is what it directly costs to deliver what you sell. Fixed operating costs stay roughly level month to month &mdash; rent, salaries, software, insurance. Other/variable costs are everything that moves with activity &mdash; marketing, travel, supplies. Getting transactions into the right bucket is exactly the discipline good bookkeeping provides, which is why a budget is only as honest as the books under it.</p>
      <p>This worksheet is a single-month snapshot. A real budget is built once, then tracked against actuals every month and rolled forward as a forecast &mdash; that&rsquo;s a budgeting-and-forecasting engagement, not a one-page tool. Use this to frame the conversation, not to replace it. It&rsquo;s a model of your inputs, not advice.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-grid" role="img" aria-label="From your own numbers, to an instant surplus and margin, to a free discovery call, to a tracked budget built on your real books.">
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP 1</div><h3>Your own numbers</h3><p>in your browser</p></div>
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP 2</div><h3>Surplus &amp; margin</h3><p>instant, honest math</p></div>
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP 3</div><h3>Free discovery call</h3><p>30 min &middot; no obligation</p></div>
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n process-step__n--done">STEP 4 &check;</div><h3>A tracked budget</h3><p>on your real books</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

